<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idab0973f9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s8048"><num value="8048">§ 8048.</num><heading> Medical Officer of the Marine Corps</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idab0973fa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s8048/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> There is a Medical Officer of the Marine Corps who shall be appointed from among flag officers of the Navy.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idab0973fb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s8048/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The Medical Officer of the Marine Corps, while so serving, shall hold the grade of rear admiral (lower half).</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idab0973fc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/118/159/dA/tV/s509B/a/1">Pub. L. 118–159, div. A, title V, § 509B(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="2024-12-23">Dec. 23, 2024</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/138/1872">138 Stat. 1872</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
